</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC248ABDD3FF66DD401F8EA06B" blockId="148.[151,1437,152,912]" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FF66DD401AFCA01D" bold="true" box="[198,451,770,796]" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F248ABDD3FE63DD401982A01C" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1982" box="[451,701,770,797]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuissima">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FE63DD401982A01C" box="[451,701,770,797]" italics="true" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Geonoma tenuissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F248ABDD3FC1DDD401FB9A01D" authorityName="Henderson, Borchsenius &amp; Balslev" authorityYear="2008" box="[957,1158,770,796]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanata">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FC1DDD401FB9A01D" box="[957,1158,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Geonoma lanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. It appears most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F248ABDD3FEB2DD6B1A95A042" authorityName="de Nevers &amp; Grayum" authorityYear="1995" box="[274,426,809,835]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mooreana">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FEB2DD6B1A95A042" box="[274,426,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">G. mooreana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F248ABDD3FE46DD6B1950A042" authorityName="Grayum &amp; de Nevers" authorityYear="1988" box="[486,623,809,835]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="148" pageNumber="149" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scoparia">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FE46DD6B1950A042" box="[486,623,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">G. scoparia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the former by its proximal and distal lips which are joined to form a raised cupule; and from the latter in its yellowish and smooth internodes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC248ABDD3FF66DD341E7AA091" blockId="148.[151,1437,152,912]" box="[198,1349,886,912]" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE248ABDD3FF66DD341ACBA091" bold="true" box="[198,500,886,912]" pageId="148" pageNumber="149">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
No trait varies within species, nor is there any geographic discontinuity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
